Listing Agent Company: Century 21 Legacy Gp
Description: Looking for your next vacation rental, with great proximity to Gatlinburg, Pigeon Forge, and Sevierville.... Look no further!!  This house has so much to offer!! This is a well-kept recently updated turn-key home ready for immediate rental or for use as a beautiful vacation or retirement home. This house has many unique features including a full-house Generac propane generator (installed 2018) that self-checks every Saturday and keeps this house fully functional and comfortable through any type of weather. The newly renovated kitchen features exotic stone counters, custom made solid wood cabinets and a unique rock wall. The stainless steel appliances (all new within the 2 years) features an under-the-counter microwave and a dual oven. The kitchen also features a large stainless steel farmhouse sink with a reverse osmosis drinking water system. The walk-in pantry easily stocks enough food for months and the adjoining laundry room has a full-size washer and dryer unit (2 years old) and plenty of shelves for storage. The house has had plumbing and electrical updates throughout within last 2-3 years. The beautiful copper colored metal roof (installed 3 years ago) showcases the rock exterior. New gutters installed same time as the metal roof (3years ago). The large 16' wide side deck wraps around to the deck at the front of the house and the other entry door. The exterior stair system allows easy access to the stand-up crawl space and to the lower yard. The interior is fully furnished with large comfortable reclining chairs, king-size memory foam beds and custom cabinets. The sturdy locally made spiral staircase is a beautiful and unique focal point and all the furnishings have been to designed to show off and blend with its beauty.  The living room and other areas were renovated and painted last year. The spacious loft area upstairs features a custom-made trundle bed (which becomes two single beds) and comfortable chairs to enjoy the propane fireplace with a decorative antique store find fireplace mantle, and an ADT security system installed in the home. Comes fully furnished with a few items that do not convey.

Listing Agent Company: Realty Works, LLC
Description: Don't miss this opportunity to own a piece of the Smoky Mountains.  Gorgeous turn key cabin secluded in the woods and perched upon a hill overlooking the river in Walland.  Seasonal views and very private setting allow for year round enjoyment of the outdoors and nature. House has 3 bedrooms, 2 baths on main with finished walk out basement and garage on lower level. Back deck has above ground swimming pool with decking.  Enjoy the large front covered porch. Small cabin could be workshop, studio or guest cabin. New solar system and generac generator. Driveway faces South and is steep in one spot, but is paved, grooved and drivable with an all wheel/front wheel vehicle. Provides lots of privacy and could be gated if desired. Almost 3 acres of outdoor hikers paradise.

Listing Agent Company: Exp Realty, LLC Nashville
Description: Fabulous newly renovated cabin secluded on 1+ acres in Wears Valley.  This property is turn-key and ready to rent! The sewer is permitted for two bedrooms but the property comfortably sleeps 11 in 2 bedrooms and 3 additional tastefully appointed bonus rooms on the 2nd floor. The interior features all new flooring, wall finishes, fixtures and furniture as well as Wi-Fi Enabled door locks and thermostats.  The kitchen is a cooks dream and features a 5-burner gas Bertazoni stove and Braun refrigerator, dishes, utensils, and small appliances.  The exterior features new metal roofing, freshly stained siding and decks, new deck furniture, and a new 6-person hot tub. Basement features a fully encapsulated crawl space with unfinished area that will be perfect for a home theater addition.  Outside, there is a detached game room with brand new foosball and air hockey tables and a detached two car garage.  This beautiful property is secluded from the hustle and bustle, yet just minutes from 321, making it convenient to popular tourist attractions in Wears Valley, Pigeon Forge, Gatlinburg and Townsend. Buyer can also join the Honeysuckle Meadows Pool and Clubhouse just minutes away at the entry to Happy Hollow Rd for a nominal annual fee.   Membership benefits extend to overnight guests. This property went live as a rental in December 2021 and generated more than $14,000 in revenue. Property features a leased water filtration system than can be continued by the new owner.

Listing Agent Company: Town & Country Realty - Downtown
Description: Investment opportunity!  This spacious 4BR and one bath home is turn-key, with a current renter paying $900 a month.  It has a new water heater, heat pump w/a 10yr warranty, updated bathroom, and new plex plumbing throughout.  It has 1480 finished square feet on the main level, with a 1400+ sq ft bonus room on the second floor that would be ideal for storage.  It has a fenced front yard and a large carport located at the back of the house.   It is located close to Holston Valley Hospital, downtown, and Stone Drive.   Buyer/buyer's agent to verify all information.  This home is sold ''As-is,'' and the Seller makes no representations or warranties as to the property condition.

Listing Agent Company: Your Home Sold Guaranteed Realty
Description: Unbelievable Views & Prime Location! Beautiful mountain chalet perched above Pigeon Forge, minutes to downtown Gatlinburg. Make this cash flow, turn-key property your next investment or residence in the Smoky Mountains. Private paved driveway with level parking. Main level features living room with gas fireplace, ample sized kitchen with island, and adjacent dinning area. Off of the kitchen, enjoy the large deck with hot tub. Second floor boasts 2 spacious bedrooms with en-suite baths, including jetted tubs. Access to the second level deck off of the primary bedroom. Upgrades include new flooring, paint, electrical, plumbing, roof, and gutters. All of this with no HOA or city taxes. Book your showing today!
